B.F.Goodrich Co. don yarn for di third quarter sey na 34% increase for polyvinyl chloride material, di company biggest customer group.

Net fell to $40.1 million, or $1.50 a share, from $60.7 million, or $2.32 a share since last year.

For di quarter, e fall 2.7% to 601.3 million from di $618.1 million.

"Polyvinyl chloride capacity don overtake demand, we dey experience reduced profit margin as a result of dat one", John D. Ong, wey be di chairman, and chief executive.

Prices for general purpose, PVC resin don drop more than 15% since December.

Di resin wey dem dey use for different different area dey use am like wall, pipe and electrical.

Goodrichi sell yarn wey be sey na di quarter of $30.1 million, less dan half of di $64.1 million wey be sey dey di quarter.

Di thirdquarter operating profit from di main chemical group go down small to $24.3 million from $24.9 million.

But operating profit from aerospace come go up to almost 50% to $15 million from di $10.1 million.

For New York Stock Exchange composite trading, Akron, Ohio based company fall from $1.375 to $49.125.

